2088
2089static expr_ty
2090ast_for_atom(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2091{
2092 /* atom: '(' [yield_expr|testlist_comp] ')' | '[' [testlist_comp] ']'
2093 | '{' [dictmaker|testlist_comp] '}' | NAME | NUMBER | STRING+
2094 | '...' | 'None' | 'True' | 'False'
2095 */
2096 node *ch = CHILD(n, 0);
2097
2098 switch (TYPE(ch)) {
2099 case NAME: {
2100 PyObject *name;
2101 const char *s = STR(ch);
2102 size_t len = strlen(s);
2103 if (len >= 4 && len <= 5) {
2104 if (!strcmp(s, "None"))
2105 return NameConstant(Py_None, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2106 if (!strcmp(s, "True"))
2107 return NameConstant(Py_True, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2108 if (!strcmp(s, "False"))
2109 return NameConstant(Py_False, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2110 }
2111 name = new_identifier(s, c);
2112 if (!name)
2113 return NULL;
2114 /* All names start in Load context, but may later be changed. */
2115 return Name(name, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2116 }
2117 case STRING: {
2118 expr_ty str = parsestrplus(c, n);
2119 if (!str) {
2120 const char *errtype = NULL;
2121 if (PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_UnicodeError))
2122 errtype = "unicode error";
2123 else if (PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_ValueError))
2124 errtype = "value error";
2125 if (errtype) {
2126 char buf[128];
2127 const char *s = NULL;
2128 PyObject *type, *value, *tback, *errstr;
2129 PyErr_Fetch(&type, &value, &tback);
2130 errstr = PyObject_Str(value);
2131 if (errstr)
2132 s = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(errstr);
2133 if (s) {
2134 PyOS_snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "(%s) %s", errtype, s);
2135 } else {
2136 PyErr_Clear();
2137 PyOS_snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "(%s) unknown error", errtype);
2138 }
2139 Py_XDECREF(errstr);
2140 ast_error(c, n, buf);
2141 Py_DECREF(type);
2142 Py_XDECREF(value);
2143 Py_XDECREF(tback);
2144 }
2145 return NULL;
2146 }
2147 return str;
2148 }
2149 case NUMBER: {
2150 PyObject *pynum = parsenumber(c, STR(ch));
2151 if (!pynum)
2152 return NULL;
2153
2154 if (PyArena_AddPyObject(c->c_arena, pynum) < 0) {
2155 Py_DECREF(pynum);
2156 return NULL;
2157 }
2158 return Num(pynum, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2159 }
2160 case ELLIPSIS: /* Ellipsis */
2161 return Ellipsis(LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2162 case LPAR: /* some parenthesized expressions */
2163 ch = CHILD(n, 1);
2164
2165 if (TYPE(ch) == RPAR)
2166 return Tuple(NULL, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2167
2168 if (TYPE(ch) == yield_expr)
2169 return ast_for_expr(c, ch);
2170
2171 /* testlist_comp: test ( comp_for | (',' test)* [','] ) */
2172 if ((NCH(ch) > 1) && (TYPE(CHILD(ch, 1)) == comp_for))
2173 return ast_for_genexp(c, ch);
2174
2175 return ast_for_testlist(c, ch);
2176 case LSQB: /* list (or list comprehension) */
2177 ch = CHILD(n, 1);
2178
2179 if (TYPE(ch) == RSQB)
2180 return List(NULL, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2181
2182 REQ(ch, testlist_comp);
2183 if (NCH(ch) == 1 || TYPE(CHILD(ch, 1)) == COMMA) {
2184 asdl_seq *elts = seq_for_testlist(c, ch);
2185 if (!elts)
2186 return NULL;
2187
2188 return List(elts, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2189 }
2190 else
2191 return ast_for_listcomp(c, ch);
2192 case LBRACE: {
2193 /* dictorsetmaker: ( ((test ':' test | '**' test)
2194 * (comp_for | (',' (test ':' test | '**' test))* [','])) |
2195 * ((test | '*' test)
2196 * (comp_for | (',' (test | '*' test))* [','])) ) */
2197 expr_ty res;
2198 ch = CHILD(n, 1);
2199 if (TYPE(ch) == RBRACE) {
2200 /* It's an empty dict. */
2201 return Dict(NULL, NULL, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2202 }
2203 else {
2204 int is_dict = (TYPE(CHILD(ch, 0)) == DOUBLESTAR);
2205 if (NCH(ch) == 1 ||
2206 (NCH(ch) > 1 &&
2207 TYPE(CHILD(ch, 1)) == COMMA)) {
2208 /* It's a set display. */
2209 res = ast_for_setdisplay(c, ch);
2210 }
2211 else if (NCH(ch) > 1 &&
2212 TYPE(CHILD(ch, 1)) == comp_for) {
2213 /* It's a set comprehension. */
2214 res = ast_for_setcomp(c, ch);
2215 }
2216 else if (NCH(ch) > 3 - is_dict &&
2217 TYPE(CHILD(ch, 3 - is_dict)) == comp_for) {
2218 /* It's a dictionary comprehension. */
2219 if (is_dict) {
2220 ast_error(c, n, "dict unpacking cannot be used in "
2221 "dict comprehension");
2222 return NULL;
2223 }
2224 res = ast_for_dictcomp(c, ch);
2225 }
2226 else {
2227 /* It's a dictionary display. */
2228 res = ast_for_dictdisplay(c, ch);
2229 }
2230 if (res) {
2231 res->lineno = LINENO(n);
2232 res->col_offset = n->n_col_offset;
2233 }
2234 return res;
2235 }
2236 }
2237 default:
2238 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError, "unhandled atom %d", TYPE(ch));
2239 return NULL;
2240 }
2241}
2242
2243static slice_ty
2244ast_for_slice(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2245{
2246 node *ch;
2247 expr_ty lower = NULL, upper = NULL, step = NULL;
2248
2249 REQ(n, subscript);
2250
2251 /*
2252 subscript: test | [test] ':' [test] [sliceop]
2253 sliceop: ':' [test]
2254 */
2255 ch = CHILD(n, 0);
2256 if (NCH(n) == 1 && TYPE(ch) == test) {
2257 /* 'step' variable hold no significance in terms of being used over
2258 other vars */
2259 step = ast_for_expr(c, ch);
2260 if (!step)
2261 return NULL;
2262
2263 return Index(step, c->c_arena);
2264 }
2265
2266 if (TYPE(ch) == test) {
2267 lower = ast_for_expr(c, ch);
2268 if (!lower)
2269 return NULL;
2270 }
2271
2272 /* If there's an upper bound it's in the second or third position. */
2273 if (TYPE(ch) == COLON) {
2274 if (NCH(n) > 1) {
2275 node *n2 = CHILD(n, 1);
2276
2277 if (TYPE(n2) == test) {
2278 upper = ast_for_expr(c, n2);
2279 if (!upper)
2280 return NULL;
2281 }
2282 }
2283 } else if (NCH(n) > 2) {
2284 node *n2 = CHILD(n, 2);
2285
2286 if (TYPE(n2) == test) {
2287 upper = ast_for_expr(c, n2);
2288 if (!upper)
2289 return NULL;
2290 }
2291 }
2292
2293 ch = CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 1);
2294 if (TYPE(ch) == sliceop) {
2295 if (NCH(ch) != 1) {
2296 ch = CHILD(ch, 1);
2297 if (TYPE(ch) == test) {
2298 step = ast_for_expr(c, ch);
2299 if (!step)
2300 return NULL;
2301 }
2302 }
2303 }
2304
2305 return Slice(lower, upper, step, c->c_arena);
2306}
2307
2308static expr_ty
2309ast_for_binop(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2310{
2311 /* Must account for a sequence of expressions.
2312 How should A op B op C by represented?
2313 BinOp(BinOp(A, op, B), op, C).
2314 */
2315
2316 int i, nops;
2317 expr_ty expr1, expr2, result;
2318 operator_ty newoperator;
2319
2320 expr1 = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 0));
2321 if (!expr1)
2322 return NULL;
2323
2324 expr2 = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 2));
2325 if (!expr2)
2326 return NULL;
2327
2328 newoperator = get_operator(CHILD(n, 1));
2329 if (!newoperator)
2330 return NULL;
2331
2332 result = BinOp(expr1, newoperator, expr2, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
2333 c->c_arena);
2334 if (!result)
2335 return NULL;
2336
2337 nops = (NCH(n) - 1) / 2;
2338 for (i = 1; i < nops; i++) {
2339 expr_ty tmp_result, tmp;
2340 const node* next_oper = CHILD(n, i * 2 + 1);
2341
2342 newoperator = get_operator(next_oper);
2343 if (!newoperator)
2344 return NULL;
2345
2346 tmp = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, i * 2 + 2));
2347 if (!tmp)
2348 return NULL;
2349
2350 tmp_result = BinOp(result, newoperator, tmp,
2351 LINENO(next_oper), next_oper->n_col_offset,
2352 c->c_arena);
2353 if (!tmp_result)
2354 return NULL;
2355 result = tmp_result;
2356 }
2357 return result;
2358}
2359
2360static expr_ty
2361ast_for_trailer(struct compiling *c, const node *n, expr_ty left_expr)
2362{
2363 /* trailer: '(' [arglist] ')' | '[' subscriptlist ']' | '.' NAME
2364 subscriptlist: subscript (',' subscript)* [',']
2365 subscript: '.' '.' '.' | test | [test] ':' [test] [sliceop]
2366 */
2367 REQ(n, trailer);
2368 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, 0)) == LPAR) {
2369 if (NCH(n) == 2)
2370 return Call(left_expr, NULL, NULL, LINENO(n),
2371 n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2372 else
2373 return ast_for_call(c, CHILD(n, 1), left_expr);
2374 }
2375 else if (TYPE(CHILD(n, 0)) == DOT) {
2376 PyObject *attr_id = NEW_IDENTIFIER(CHILD(n, 1));
2377 if (!attr_id)
2378 return NULL;
2379 return Attribute(left_expr, attr_id, Load,
2380 LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2381 }
2382 else {
2383 REQ(CHILD(n, 0), LSQB);
2384 REQ(CHILD(n, 2), RSQB);
2385 n = CHILD(n, 1);
2386 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
2387 slice_ty slc = ast_for_slice(c, CHILD(n, 0));
2388 if (!slc)
2389 return NULL;
2390 return Subscript(left_expr, slc, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
2391 c->c_arena);
2392 }
2393 else {
2394 /* The grammar is ambiguous here. The ambiguity is resolved
2395 by treating the sequence as a tuple literal if there are
2396 no slice features.
2397 */
2398 int j;
2399 slice_ty slc;
2400 expr_ty e;
2401 int simple = 1;
2402 asdl_seq *slices, *elts;
2403 slices = _Py_asdl_seq_new((NCH(n) + 1) / 2, c->c_arena);
2404 if (!slices)
2405 return NULL;
2406 for (j = 0; j < NCH(n); j += 2) {
2407 slc = ast_for_slice(c, CHILD(n, j));
2408 if (!slc)
2409 return NULL;
2410 if (slc->kind != Index_kind)
2411 simple = 0;
2412 asdl_seq_SET(slices, j / 2, slc);
2413 }
2414 if (!simple) {
2415 return Subscript(left_expr, ExtSlice(slices, c->c_arena),
2416 Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2417 }
2418 /* extract Index values and put them in a Tuple */
2419 elts = _Py_asdl_seq_new(asdl_seq_LEN(slices), c->c_arena);
2420 if (!elts)
2421 return NULL;
2422 for (j = 0; j < asdl_seq_LEN(slices); ++j) {
2423 slc = (slice_ty)asdl_seq_GET(slices, j);
2424 assert(slc->kind == Index_kind && slc->v.Index.value);
2425 asdl_seq_SET(elts, j, slc->v.Index.value);
2426 }
2427 e = Tuple(elts, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2428 if (!e)
2429 return NULL;
2430 return Subscript(left_expr, Index(e, c->c_arena),
2431 Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2432 }
2433 }
2434}
2435
2436static expr_ty
2437ast_for_factor(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2438{
2439 expr_ty expression;
2440
2441 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
2442 if (!expression)
2443 return NULL;
2444
2445 switch (TYPE(CHILD(n, 0))) {
2446 case PLUS:
2447 return UnaryOp(UAdd, expression, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
2448 c->c_arena);
2449 case MINUS:
2450 return UnaryOp(USub, expression, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
2451 c->c_arena);
2452 case TILDE:
2453 return UnaryOp(Invert, expression, LINENO(n),
2454 n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2455 }
2456 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError, "unhandled factor: %d",
2457 TYPE(CHILD(n, 0)));
2458 return NULL;
2459}
2460
2461static expr_ty
2462ast_for_atom_expr(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2463{
2464 int i, nch, start = 0;
2465 expr_ty e, tmp;
2466
2467 REQ(n, atom_expr);
2468 nch = NCH(n);
2469
2470 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, 0)) == AWAIT) {
2471 start = 1;
2472 assert(nch > 1);
2473 }
2474
2475 e = ast_for_atom(c, CHILD(n, start));
2476 if (!e)
2477 return NULL;
2478 if (nch == 1)
2479 return e;
2480 if (start && nch == 2) {
2481 return Await(e, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2482 }
2483
2484 for (i = start + 1; i < nch; i++) {
2485 node *ch = CHILD(n, i);
2486 if (TYPE(ch) != trailer)
2487 break;
2488 tmp = ast_for_trailer(c, ch, e);
2489 if (!tmp)
2490 return NULL;
2491 tmp->lineno = e->lineno;
2492 tmp->col_offset = e->col_offset;
2493 e = tmp;
2494 }
2495
2496 if (start) {
2497 /* there was an AWAIT */
2498 return Await(e, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2499 }
2500 else {
2501 return e;
2502 }
2503}
2504
2505static expr_ty
2506ast_for_power(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2507{
2508 /* power: atom trailer* ('**' factor)*
2509 */
2510 expr_ty e;
2511 REQ(n, power);
2512 e = ast_for_atom_expr(c, CHILD(n, 0));
2513 if (!e)
2514 return NULL;
2515 if (NCH(n) == 1)
2516 return e;
2517 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 1)) == factor) {
2518 expr_ty f = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 1));
2519 if (!f)
2520 return NULL;
2521 e = BinOp(e, Pow, f, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2522 }
2523 return e;
2524}
2525
2526static expr_ty
2527ast_for_starred(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2528{
2529 expr_ty tmp;
2530 REQ(n, star_expr);
2531
2532 tmp = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
2533 if (!tmp)
2534 return NULL;
2535
2536 /* The Load context is changed later. */
2537 return Starred(tmp, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2538}
2539
2540
2541/* Do not name a variable 'expr'! Will cause a compile error.
2542*/
2543
2544static expr_ty
2545ast_for_expr(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2546{
2547 /* handle the full range of simple expressions
2548 test: or_test ['if' or_test 'else' test] | lambdef
2549 test_nocond: or_test | lambdef_nocond
2550 or_test: and_test ('or' and_test)*
2551 and_test: not_test ('and' not_test)*
2552 not_test: 'not' not_test | comparison
2553 comparison: expr (comp_op expr)*
2554 expr: xor_expr ('|' xor_expr)*
2555 xor_expr: and_expr ('^' and_expr)*
2556 and_expr: shift_expr ('&' shift_expr)*
2557 shift_expr: arith_expr (('<<'|'>>') arith_expr)*
2558 arith_expr: term (('+'|'-') term)*
2559 term: factor (('*'|'@'|'/'|'%'|'//') factor)*
2560 factor: ('+'|'-'|'~') factor | power
2561 power: atom_expr ['**' factor]
2562 atom_expr: [AWAIT] atom trailer*
2563 yield_expr: 'yield' [yield_arg]
2564 */
2565
2566 asdl_seq *seq;
2567 int i;
2568
2569 loop:
2570 switch (TYPE(n)) {
2571 case test:
2572 case test_nocond:
2573 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, 0)) == lambdef ||
2574 TYPE(CHILD(n, 0)) == lambdef_nocond)
2575 return ast_for_lambdef(c, CHILD(n, 0));
2576 else if (NCH(n) > 1)
2577 return ast_for_ifexpr(c, n);
2578 /* Fallthrough */
2579 case or_test:
2580 case and_test:
2581 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
2582 n = CHILD(n, 0);
2583 goto loop;
2584 }
2585 seq = _Py_asdl_seq_new((NCH(n) + 1) / 2, c->c_arena);
2586 if (!seq)
2587 return NULL;
2588 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n); i += 2) {
2589 expr_ty e = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, i));
2590 if (!e)
2591 return NULL;
2592 asdl_seq_SET(seq, i / 2, e);
2593 }
2594 if (!strcmp(STR(CHILD(n, 1)), "and"))
2595 return BoolOp(And, seq, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
2596 c->c_arena);
2597 assert(!strcmp(STR(CHILD(n, 1)), "or"));
2598 return BoolOp(Or, seq, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2599 case not_test:
2600 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
2601 n = CHILD(n, 0);
2602 goto loop;
2603 }
2604 else {
2605 expr_ty expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
2606 if (!expression)
2607 return NULL;
2608
2609 return UnaryOp(Not, expression, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
2610 c->c_arena);
2611 }
2612 case comparison:
2613 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
2614 n = CHILD(n, 0);
2615 goto loop;
2616 }
2617 else {
2618 expr_ty expression;
2619 asdl_int_seq *ops;
2620 asdl_seq *cmps;
2621 ops = _Py_asdl_int_seq_new(NCH(n) / 2, c->c_arena);
2622 if (!ops)
2623 return NULL;
2624 cmps = _Py_asdl_seq_new(NCH(n) / 2, c->c_arena);
2625 if (!cmps) {
2626 return NULL;
2627 }
2628 for (i = 1; i < NCH(n); i += 2) {
2629 cmpop_ty newoperator;
2630
2631 newoperator = ast_for_comp_op(c, CHILD(n, i));
2632 if (!newoperator) {
2633 return NULL;
2634 }
2635
2636 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, i + 1));
2637 if (!expression) {
2638 return NULL;
2639 }
2640
2641 asdl_seq_SET(ops, i / 2, newoperator);
2642 asdl_seq_SET(cmps, i / 2, expression);
2643 }
2644 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 0));
2645 if (!expression) {
2646 return NULL;
2647 }
2648
2649 return Compare(expression, ops, cmps, LINENO(n),
2650 n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2651 }
2652 break;
2653
2654 case star_expr:
2655 return ast_for_starred(c, n);
2656 /* The next five cases all handle BinOps. The main body of code
2657 is the same in each case, but the switch turned inside out to
2658 reuse the code for each type of operator.
2659 */
2660 case expr:
2661 case xor_expr:
2662 case and_expr:
2663 case shift_expr:
2664 case arith_expr:
2665 case term:
2666 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
2667 n = CHILD(n, 0);
2668 goto loop;
2669 }
2670 return ast_for_binop(c, n);
2671 case yield_expr: {
2672 node *an = NULL;
2673 node *en = NULL;
2674 int is_from = 0;
2675 expr_ty exp = NULL;
2676 if (NCH(n) > 1)
2677 an = CHILD(n, 1); /* yield_arg */
2678 if (an) {
2679 en = CHILD(an, NCH(an) - 1);
2680 if (NCH(an) == 2) {
2681 is_from = 1;
2682 exp = ast_for_expr(c, en);
2683 }
2684 else
2685 exp = ast_for_testlist(c, en);
2686 if (!exp)
2687 return NULL;
2688 }
2689 if (is_from)
2690 return YieldFrom(exp, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2691 return Yield(exp, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2692 }
2693 case factor:
2694 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
2695 n = CHILD(n, 0);
2696 goto loop;
2697 }
2698 return ast_for_factor(c, n);
2699 case power:
2700 return ast_for_power(c, n);
2701 default:
2702 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError, "unhandled expr: %d", TYPE(n));
2703 return NULL;
2704 }
2705 /* should never get here unless if error is set */
2706 return NULL;
2707}
2708
2709static expr_ty
2710ast_for_call(struct compiling *c, const node *n, expr_ty func)
2711{
2712 /*
2713 arglist: argument (',' argument)* [',']
2714 argument: ( test [comp_for] | '*' test | test '=' test | '**' test )
2715 */
2716
2717 int i, nargs, nkeywords, ngens;
2718 int ndoublestars;
2719 asdl_seq *args;
2720 asdl_seq *keywords;
2721
2722 REQ(n, arglist);
2723
2724 nargs = 0;
2725 nkeywords = 0;
2726 ngens = 0;
2727 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n); i++) {
2728 node *ch = CHILD(n, i);
2729 if (TYPE(ch) == argument) {
2730 if (NCH(ch) == 1)
2731 nargs++;
2732 else if (TYPE(CHILD(ch, 1)) == comp_for)
2733 ngens++;
2734 else if (TYPE(CHILD(ch, 0)) == STAR)
2735 nargs++;
2736 else
2737 /* TYPE(CHILD(ch, 0)) == DOUBLESTAR or keyword argument */
2738 nkeywords++;
2739 }
2740 }
2741 if (ngens > 1 || (ngens && (nargs || nkeywords))) {
2742 ast_error(c, n, "Generator expression must be parenthesized "
2743 "if not sole argument");
2744 return NULL;
2745 }
2746
2747 args = _Py_asdl_seq_new(nargs + ngens, c->c_arena);
2748 if (!args)
2749 return NULL;
2750 keywords = _Py_asdl_seq_new(nkeywords, c->c_arena);
2751 if (!keywords)
2752 return NULL;
2753
2754 nargs = 0; /* positional arguments + iterable argument unpackings */
2755 nkeywords = 0; /* keyword arguments + keyword argument unpackings */
2756 ndoublestars = 0; /* just keyword argument unpackings */
2757 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n); i++) {
2758 node *ch = CHILD(n, i);
2759 if (TYPE(ch) == argument) {
2760 expr_ty e;
2761 node *chch = CHILD(ch, 0);
2762 if (NCH(ch) == 1) {
2763 /* a positional argument */
2764 if (nkeywords) {
2765 if (ndoublestars) {
2766 ast_error(c, chch,
2767 "positional argument follows "
2768 "keyword argument unpacking");
2769 }
2770 else {
2771 ast_error(c, chch,
2772 "positional argument follows "
2773 "keyword argument");
2774 }
2775 return NULL;
2776 }
2777 e = ast_for_expr(c, chch);
2778 if (!e)
2779 return NULL;
2780 asdl_seq_SET(args, nargs++, e);
2781 }
2782 else if (TYPE(chch) == STAR) {
2783 /* an iterable argument unpacking */
2784 expr_ty starred;
2785 if (ndoublestars) {
2786 ast_error(c, chch,
2787 "iterable argument unpacking follows "
2788 "keyword argument unpacking");
2789 return NULL;
2790 }
2791 e = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(ch, 1));
2792 if (!e)
2793 return NULL;
2794 starred = Starred(e, Load, LINENO(chch),
2795 chch->n_col_offset,
2796 c->c_arena);
2797 if (!starred)
2798 return NULL;
2799 asdl_seq_SET(args, nargs++, starred);
2800
2801 }
2802 else if (TYPE(chch) == DOUBLESTAR) {
2803 /* a keyword argument unpacking */
2804 keyword_ty kw;
2805 i++;
2806 e = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(ch, 1));
2807 if (!e)
2808 return NULL;
2809 kw = keyword(NULL, e, c->c_arena);
2810 asdl_seq_SET(keywords, nkeywords++, kw);
2811 ndoublestars++;
2812 }
2813 else if (TYPE(CHILD(ch, 1)) == comp_for) {
2814 /* the lone generator expression */
2815 e = ast_for_genexp(c, ch);
2816 if (!e)
2817 return NULL;
2818 asdl_seq_SET(args, nargs++, e);
2819 }
2820 else {
2821 /* a keyword argument */
2822 keyword_ty kw;
2823 identifier key, tmp;
2824 int k;
2825
2826 /* chch is test, but must be an identifier? */
2827 e = ast_for_expr(c, chch);
2828 if (!e)
2829 return NULL;
2830 /* f(lambda x: x[0] = 3) ends up getting parsed with
2831 * LHS test = lambda x: x[0], and RHS test = 3.
2832 * SF bug 132313 points out that complaining about a keyword
2833 * then is very confusing.
2834 */
2835 if (e->kind == Lambda_kind) {
2836 ast_error(c, chch,
2837 "lambda cannot contain assignment");
2838 return NULL;
2839 }
2840 else if (e->kind != Name_kind) {
2841 ast_error(c, chch,
2842 "keyword can't be an expression");
2843 return NULL;
2844 }
2845 else if (forbidden_name(c, e->v.Name.id, ch, 1)) {
2846 return NULL;
2847 }
2848 key = e->v.Name.id;
2849 for (k = 0; k < nkeywords; k++) {
2850 tmp = ((keyword_ty)asdl_seq_GET(keywords, k))->arg;
2851 if (tmp && !PyUnicode_Compare(tmp, key)) {
2852 ast_error(c, chch,
2853 "keyword argument repeated");
2854 return NULL;
2855 }
2856 }
2857 e = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(ch, 2));
2858 if (!e)
2859 return NULL;
2860 kw = keyword(key, e, c->c_arena);
2861 if (!kw)
2862 return NULL;
2863 asdl_seq_SET(keywords, nkeywords++, kw);
2864 }
2865 }
2866 }
2867
2868 return Call(func, args, keywords, func->lineno, func->col_offset, c->c_arena);
2869}
2870
2871static expr_ty
2872ast_for_testlist(struct compiling *c, const node* n)
2873{
2874 /* testlist_comp: test (comp_for | (',' test)* [',']) */
2875 /* testlist: test (',' test)* [','] */
2876 assert(NCH(n) > 0);
2877 if (TYPE(n) == testlist_comp) {
2878 if (NCH(n) > 1)
2879 assert(TYPE(CHILD(n, 1)) != comp_for);
2880 }
2881 else {
2882 assert(TYPE(n) == testlist ||
2883 TYPE(n) == testlist_star_expr);
2884 }
2885 if (NCH(n) == 1)
2886 return ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 0));
2887 else {
2888 asdl_seq *tmp = seq_for_testlist(c, n);
2889 if (!tmp)
2890 return NULL;
2891 return Tuple(tmp, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2892 }
2893}
2894
2895static stmt_ty
2896ast_for_expr_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
2897{
2898 REQ(n, expr_stmt);
2899 /* expr_stmt: testlist_star_expr (annassign | augassign (yield_expr|testlist) |
2900 ('=' (yield_expr|testlist_star_expr))*)
2901 annassign: ':' test ['=' test]
2902 testlist_star_expr: (test|star_expr) (',' test|star_expr)* [',']
2903 augassign: '+=' | '-=' | '*=' | '@=' | '/=' | '%=' | '&=' | '|=' | '^='
2904 | '<<=' | '>>=' | '**=' | '//='
2905 test: ... here starts the operator precedence dance
2906 */
2907
2908 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
2909 expr_ty e = ast_for_testlist(c, CHILD(n, 0));
2910 if (!e)
2911 return NULL;
2912
2913 return Expr(e, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2914 }
2915 else if (TYPE(CHILD(n, 1)) == augassign) {
2916 expr_ty expr1, expr2;
2917 operator_ty newoperator;
2918 node *ch = CHILD(n, 0);
2919
2920 expr1 = ast_for_testlist(c, ch);
2921 if (!expr1)
2922 return NULL;
2923 if(!set_context(c, expr1, Store, ch))
2924 return NULL;
2925 /* set_context checks that most expressions are not the left side.
2926 Augmented assignments can only have a name, a subscript, or an
2927 attribute on the left, though, so we have to explicitly check for
2928 those. */
2929 switch (expr1->kind) {
2930 case Name_kind:
2931 case Attribute_kind:
2932 case Subscript_kind:
2933 break;
2934 default:
2935 ast_error(c, ch, "illegal expression for augmented assignment");
2936 return NULL;
2937 }
2938
2939 ch = CHILD(n, 2);
2940 if (TYPE(ch) == testlist)
2941 expr2 = ast_for_testlist(c, ch);
2942 else
2943 expr2 = ast_for_expr(c, ch);
2944 if (!expr2)
2945 return NULL;
2946
2947 newoperator = ast_for_augassign(c, CHILD(n, 1));
2948 if (!newoperator)
2949 return NULL;
2950
2951 return AugAssign(expr1, newoperator, expr2, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
2952 }
2953 else if (TYPE(CHILD(n, 1)) == annassign) {
2954 expr_ty expr1, expr2, expr3;
2955 node *ch = CHILD(n, 0);
2956 node *deep, *ann = CHILD(n, 1);
2957 int simple = 1;
2958
2959 /* we keep track of parens to qualify (x) as expression not name */
2960 deep = ch;
2961 while (NCH(deep) == 1) {
2962 deep = CHILD(deep, 0);
2963 }
2964 if (NCH(deep) > 0 && TYPE(CHILD(deep, 0)) == LPAR) {
2965 simple = 0;
2966 }
2967 expr1 = ast_for_testlist(c, ch);
2968 if (!expr1) {
2969 return NULL;
2970 }
2971 switch (expr1->kind) {
2972 case Name_kind:
2973 if (forbidden_name(c, expr1->v.Name.id, n, 0)) {
2974 return NULL;
2975 }
2976 expr1->v.Name.ctx = Store;
2977 break;
2978 case Attribute_kind:
2979 if (forbidden_name(c, expr1->v.Attribute.attr, n, 1)) {
2980 return NULL;
2981 }
2982 expr1->v.Attribute.ctx = Store;
2983 break;
2984 case Subscript_kind:
2985 expr1->v.Subscript.ctx = Store;
2986 break;
2987 case List_kind:
2988 ast_error(c, ch,
2989 "only single target (not list) can be annotated");
2990 return NULL;
2991 case Tuple_kind:
2992 ast_error(c, ch,
2993 "only single target (not tuple) can be annotated");
2994 return NULL;
2995 default:
2996 ast_error(c, ch,
2997 "illegal target for annotation");
2998 return NULL;
2999 }
3000
3001 if (expr1->kind != Name_kind) {
3002 simple = 0;
3003 }
3004 ch = CHILD(ann, 1);
3005 expr2 = ast_for_expr(c, ch);
3006 if (!expr2) {
3007 return NULL;
3008 }
3009 if (NCH(ann) == 2) {
3010 return AnnAssign(expr1, expr2, NULL, simple,
3011 LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3012 }
3013 else {
3014 ch = CHILD(ann, 3);
3015 expr3 = ast_for_expr(c, ch);
3016 if (!expr3) {
3017 return NULL;
3018 }
3019 return AnnAssign(expr1, expr2, expr3, simple,
3020 LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3021 }
3022 }
3023 else {
3024 int i;
3025 asdl_seq *targets;
3026 node *value;
3027 expr_ty expression;
3028
3029 /* a normal assignment */
3030 REQ(CHILD(n, 1), EQUAL);
3031 targets = _Py_asdl_seq_new(NCH(n) / 2, c->c_arena);
3032 if (!targets)
3033 return NULL;
3034 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n) - 2; i += 2) {
3035 expr_ty e;
3036 node *ch = CHILD(n, i);
3037 if (TYPE(ch) == yield_expr) {
3038 ast_error(c, ch, "assignment to yield expression not possible");
3039 return NULL;
3040 }
3041 e = ast_for_testlist(c, ch);
3042 if (!e)
3043 return NULL;
3044
3045 /* set context to assign */
3046 if (!set_context(c, e, Store, CHILD(n, i)))
3047 return NULL;
3048
3049 asdl_seq_SET(targets, i / 2, e);
3050 }
3051 value = CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 1);
3052 if (TYPE(value) == testlist_star_expr)
3053 expression = ast_for_testlist(c, value);
3054 else
3055 expression = ast_for_expr(c, value);
3056 if (!expression)
3057 return NULL;
3058 return Assign(targets, expression, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3059 }
3060}

3062
3063static asdl_seq *
3064ast_for_exprlist(struct compiling *c, const node *n, expr_context_ty context)
3065{
3066 asdl_seq *seq;
3067 int i;
3068 expr_ty e;
3069
3070 REQ(n, exprlist);
3071
3072 seq = _Py_asdl_seq_new((NCH(n) + 1) / 2, c->c_arena);
3073 if (!seq)
3074 return NULL;
3075 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n); i += 2) {
3076 e = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, i));
3077 if (!e)
3078 return NULL;
3079 asdl_seq_SET(seq, i / 2, e);
3080 if (context && !set_context(c, e, context, CHILD(n, i)))
3081 return NULL;
3082 }
3083 return seq;
3084}

3100static stmt_ty
3101ast_for_flow_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3102{
3103 /*
3104 flow_stmt: break_stmt | continue_stmt | return_stmt | raise_stmt
3105 | yield_stmt
3106 break_stmt: 'break'
3107 continue_stmt: 'continue'
3108 return_stmt: 'return' [testlist]
3109 yield_stmt: yield_expr
3110 yield_expr: 'yield' testlist | 'yield' 'from' test
3111 raise_stmt: 'raise' [test [',' test [',' test]]]
3112 */
3113 node *ch;
3114
3115 REQ(n, flow_stmt);
3116 ch = CHILD(n, 0);
3117 switch (TYPE(ch)) {
3118 case break_stmt:
3119 return Break(LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3120 case continue_stmt:
3121 return Continue(LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3122 case yield_stmt: { /* will reduce to yield_expr */
3123 expr_ty exp = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(ch, 0));
3124 if (!exp)
3125 return NULL;
3126 return Expr(exp, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3127 }
3128 case return_stmt:
3129 if (NCH(ch) == 1)
3130 return Return(NULL, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3131 else {
3132 expr_ty expression = ast_for_testlist(c, CHILD(ch, 1));
3133 if (!expression)
3134 return NULL;
3135 return Return(expression, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3136 }
3137 case raise_stmt:
3138 if (NCH(ch) == 1)
3139 return Raise(NULL, NULL, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3140 else if (NCH(ch) >= 2) {
3141 expr_ty cause = NULL;
3142 expr_ty expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(ch, 1));
3143 if (!expression)
3144 return NULL;
3145 if (NCH(ch) == 4) {
3146 cause = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(ch, 3));
3147 if (!cause)
3148 return NULL;
3149 }
3150 return Raise(expression, cause, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3151 }
3152 /* fall through */
3153 default:
3154 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
3155 "unexpected flow_stmt: %d", TYPE(ch));
3156 return NULL;
3157 }
3158}
3159
3160static alias_ty
3161alias_for_import_name(struct compiling *c, const node *n, int store)
3162{
3163 /*
3164 import_as_name: NAME ['as' NAME]
3165 dotted_as_name: dotted_name ['as' NAME]
3166 dotted_name: NAME ('.' NAME)*
3167 */
3168 identifier str, name;
3169
3170 loop:
3171 switch (TYPE(n)) {
3172 case import_as_name: {
3173 node *name_node = CHILD(n, 0);
3174 str = NULL;
3175 name = NEW_IDENTIFIER(name_node);
3176 if (!name)
3177 return NULL;
3178 if (NCH(n) == 3) {
3179 node *str_node = CHILD(n, 2);
3180 str = NEW_IDENTIFIER(str_node);
3181 if (!str)
3182 return NULL;
3183 if (store && forbidden_name(c, str, str_node, 0))
3184 return NULL;
3185 }
3186 else {
3187 if (forbidden_name(c, name, name_node, 0))
3188 return NULL;
3189 }
3190 return alias(name, str, c->c_arena);
3191 }
3192 case dotted_as_name:
3193 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
3194 n = CHILD(n, 0);
3195 goto loop;
3196 }
3197 else {
3198 node *asname_node = CHILD(n, 2);
3199 alias_ty a = alias_for_import_name(c, CHILD(n, 0), 0);
3200 if (!a)
3201 return NULL;
3202 assert(!a->asname);
3203 a->asname = NEW_IDENTIFIER(asname_node);
3204 if (!a->asname)
3205 return NULL;
3206 if (forbidden_name(c, a->asname, asname_node, 0))
3207 return NULL;
3208 return a;
3209 }
3210 break;
3211 case dotted_name:
3212 if (NCH(n) == 1) {
3213 node *name_node = CHILD(n, 0);
3214 name = NEW_IDENTIFIER(name_node);
3215 if (!name)
3216 return NULL;
3217 if (store && forbidden_name(c, name, name_node, 0))
3218 return NULL;
3219 return alias(name, NULL, c->c_arena);
3220 }
3221 else {
3222 /* Create a string of the form "a.b.c" */
3223 int i;
3224 size_t len;
3225 char *s;
3226 PyObject *uni;
3227
3228 len = 0;
3229 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n); i += 2)
3230 /* length of string plus one for the dot */
3231 len += strlen(STR(CHILD(n, i))) + 1;
3232 len--; /* the last name doesn't have a dot */
3233 str = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(NULL, len);
3234 if (!str)
3235 return NULL;
3236 s = PyBytes_AS_STRING(str);
3237 if (!s)
3238 return NULL;
3239 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n); i += 2) {
3240 char *sch = STR(CHILD(n, i));
3241 strcpy(s, STR(CHILD(n, i)));
3242 s += strlen(sch);
3243 *s++ = '.';
3244 }
3245 --s;
3246 *s = '\0';
3247 uni = PyUnicode_DecodeUTF8(PyBytes_AS_STRING(str),
3248 PyBytes_GET_SIZE(str),
3249 NULL);
3250 Py_DECREF(str);
3251 if (!uni)
3252 return NULL;
3253 str = uni;
3254 PyUnicode_InternInPlace(&str);
3255 if (PyArena_AddPyObject(c->c_arena, str) < 0) {
3256 Py_DECREF(str);
3257 return NULL;
3258 }
3259 return alias(str, NULL, c->c_arena);
3260 }
3261 break;
3262 case STAR:
3263 str = PyUnicode_InternFromString("*");
3264 if (PyArena_AddPyObject(c->c_arena, str) < 0) {
3265 Py_DECREF(str);
3266 return NULL;
3267 }
3268 return alias(str, NULL, c->c_arena);
3269 default:
3270 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
3271 "unexpected import name: %d", TYPE(n));
3272 return NULL;
3273 }
3274
3275 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_SystemError, "unhandled import name condition");
3276 return NULL;
3277}
3278
3279static stmt_ty
3280ast_for_import_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3281{
3282 /*
3283 import_stmt: import_name | import_from
3284 import_name: 'import' dotted_as_names
3285 import_from: 'from' (('.' | '...')* dotted_name | ('.' | '...')+)
3286 'import' ('*' | '(' import_as_names ')' | import_as_names)
3287 */
3288 int lineno;
3289 int col_offset;
3290 int i;
3291 asdl_seq *aliases;
3292
3293 REQ(n, import_stmt);
3294 lineno = LINENO(n);
3295 col_offset = n->n_col_offset;
3296 n = CHILD(n, 0);
3297 if (TYPE(n) == import_name) {
3298 n = CHILD(n, 1);
3299 REQ(n, dotted_as_names);
3300 aliases = _Py_asdl_seq_new((NCH(n) + 1) / 2, c->c_arena);
3301 if (!aliases)
3302 return NULL;
3303 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n); i += 2) {
3304 alias_ty import_alias = alias_for_import_name(c, CHILD(n, i), 1);
3305 if (!import_alias)
3306 return NULL;
3307 asdl_seq_SET(aliases, i / 2, import_alias);
3308 }
3309 return Import(aliases, lineno, col_offset, c->c_arena);
3310 }
3311 else if (TYPE(n) == import_from) {
3312 int n_children;
3313 int idx, ndots = 0;
3314 alias_ty mod = NULL;
3315 identifier modname = NULL;
3316
3317 /* Count the number of dots (for relative imports) and check for the
3318 optional module name */
3319 for (idx = 1; idx < NCH(n); idx++) {
3320 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, idx)) == dotted_name) {
3321 mod = alias_for_import_name(c, CHILD(n, idx), 0);
3322 if (!mod)
3323 return NULL;
3324 idx++;
3325 break;
3326 } else if (TYPE(CHILD(n, idx)) == ELLIPSIS) {
3327 /* three consecutive dots are tokenized as one ELLIPSIS */
3328 ndots += 3;
3329 continue;
3330 } else if (TYPE(CHILD(n, idx)) != DOT) {
3331 break;
3332 }
3333 ndots++;
3334 }
3335 idx++; /* skip over the 'import' keyword */
3336 switch (TYPE(CHILD(n, idx))) {
3337 case STAR:
3338 /* from ... import * */
3339 n = CHILD(n, idx);
3340 n_children = 1;
3341 break;
3342 case LPAR:
3343 /* from ... import (x, y, z) */
3344 n = CHILD(n, idx + 1);
3345 n_children = NCH(n);
3346 break;
3347 case import_as_names:
3348 /* from ... import x, y, z */
3349 n = CHILD(n, idx);
3350 n_children = NCH(n);
3351 if (n_children % 2 == 0) {
3352 ast_error(c, n, "trailing comma not allowed without"
3353 " surrounding parentheses");
3354 return NULL;
3355 }
3356 break;
3357 default:
3358 ast_error(c, n, "Unexpected node-type in from-import");
3359 return NULL;
3360 }
3361
3362 aliases = _Py_asdl_seq_new((n_children + 1) / 2, c->c_arena);
3363 if (!aliases)
3364 return NULL;
3365
3366 /* handle "from ... import *" special b/c there's no children */
3367 if (TYPE(n) == STAR) {
3368 alias_ty import_alias = alias_for_import_name(c, n, 1);
3369 if (!import_alias)
3370 return NULL;
3371 asdl_seq_SET(aliases, 0, import_alias);
3372 }
3373 else {
3374 for (i = 0; i < NCH(n); i += 2) {
3375 alias_ty import_alias = alias_for_import_name(c, CHILD(n, i), 1);
3376 if (!import_alias)
3377 return NULL;
3378 asdl_seq_SET(aliases, i / 2, import_alias);
3379 }
3380 }
3381 if (mod != NULL)
3382 modname = mod->name;
3383 return ImportFrom(modname, aliases, ndots, lineno, col_offset,
3384 c->c_arena);
3385 }
3386 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
3387 "unknown import statement: starts with command '%s'",
3388 STR(CHILD(n, 0)));
3389 return NULL;
3390}

3406 if (!name)

3433
3434static stmt_ty
3435ast_for_assert_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3436{
3437 /* assert_stmt: 'assert' test [',' test] */
3438 REQ(n, assert_stmt);
3439 if (NCH(n) == 2) {
3440 expr_ty expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
3441 if (!expression)
3442 return NULL;
3443 return Assert(expression, NULL, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3444 }
3445 else if (NCH(n) == 4) {
3446 expr_ty expr1, expr2;
3447
3448 expr1 = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
3449 if (!expr1)
3450 return NULL;
3451 expr2 = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 3));
3452 if (!expr2)
3453 return NULL;
3454
3455 return Assert(expr1, expr2, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3456 }
3457 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
3458 "improper number of parts to 'assert' statement: %d",
3459 NCH(n));
3460 return NULL;
3461}
3462
3463static asdl_seq *
3464ast_for_suite(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3465{
3466 /* suite: simple_stmt | NEWLINE INDENT stmt+ DEDENT */
3467 asdl_seq *seq;
3468 stmt_ty s;
3469 int i, total, num, end, pos = 0;
3470 node *ch;
3471
3472 REQ(n, suite);
3473
3474 total = num_stmts(n);
3475 seq = _Py_asdl_seq_new(total, c->c_arena);
3476 if (!seq)
3477 return NULL;
3478 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, 0)) == simple_stmt) {
3479 n = CHILD(n, 0);
3480 /* simple_stmt always ends with a NEWLINE,
3481 and may have a trailing SEMI
3482 */
3483 end = NCH(n) - 1;
3484 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, end - 1)) == SEMI)
3485 end--;
3486 /* loop by 2 to skip semi-colons */
3487 for (i = 0; i < end; i += 2) {
3488 ch = CHILD(n, i);
3489 s = ast_for_stmt(c, ch);
3490 if (!s)
3491 return NULL;
3492 asdl_seq_SET(seq, pos++, s);
3493 }
3494 }
3495 else {
3496 for (i = 2; i < (NCH(n) - 1); i++) {
3497 ch = CHILD(n, i);
3498 REQ(ch, stmt);
3499 num = num_stmts(ch);
3500 if (num == 1) {
3501 /* small_stmt or compound_stmt with only one child */
3502 s = ast_for_stmt(c, ch);
3503 if (!s)
3504 return NULL;
3505 asdl_seq_SET(seq, pos++, s);
3506 }
3507 else {
3508 int j;
3509 ch = CHILD(ch, 0);
3510 REQ(ch, simple_stmt);
3511 for (j = 0; j < NCH(ch); j += 2) {
3512 /* statement terminates with a semi-colon ';' */
3513 if (NCH(CHILD(ch, j)) == 0) {
3514 assert((j + 1) == NCH(ch));
3515 break;
3516 }
3517 s = ast_for_stmt(c, CHILD(ch, j));
3518 if (!s)
3519 return NULL;
3520 asdl_seq_SET(seq, pos++, s);
3521 }
3522 }
3523 }
3524 }
3525 assert(pos == seq->size);
3526 return seq;
3527}
3528
3529static string
3530docstring_from_stmts(asdl_seq *stmts)
3531{
3532 if (stmts && stmts->size) {
3533 stmt_ty s = (stmt_ty)asdl_seq_GET(stmts, 0);
3534 /* If first statement is a literal string, it's the doc string. */
3535 if (s->kind == Expr_kind && s->v.Expr.value->kind == Str_kind) {
3536 string doc = s->v.Expr.value->v.Str.s;
3537 /* not very efficient, but simple */
3538 memmove(&asdl_seq_GET(stmts, 0), &asdl_seq_GET(stmts, 1),
3539 (stmts->size - 1) * sizeof(void*));
3540 stmts->size--;
3541 return doc;
3542 }
3543 }
3544 return NULL;
3545}
3546
3547static asdl_seq *
3548ast_for_body(struct compiling *c, const node *n, string *docstring)
3549{
3550 asdl_seq *stmts = ast_for_suite(c, n);
3551 *docstring = docstring_from_stmts(stmts);
3552 return stmts;
3553}
3554
3555static stmt_ty
3556ast_for_if_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3557{
3558 /* if_stmt: 'if' test ':' suite ('elif' test ':' suite)*
3559 ['else' ':' suite]
3560 */
3561 char *s;
3562
3563 REQ(n, if_stmt);
3564
3565 if (NCH(n) == 4) {
3566 expr_ty expression;
3567 asdl_seq *suite_seq;
3568
3569 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
3570 if (!expression)
3571 return NULL;
3572 suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 3));
3573 if (!suite_seq)
3574 return NULL;
3575
3576 return If(expression, suite_seq, NULL, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
3577 c->c_arena);
3578 }
3579
3580 s = STR(CHILD(n, 4));
3581 /* s[2], the third character in the string, will be
3582 's' for el_s_e, or
3583 'i' for el_i_f
3584 */
3585 if (s[2] == 's') {
3586 expr_ty expression;
3587 asdl_seq *seq1, *seq2;
3588
3589 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
3590 if (!expression)
3591 return NULL;
3592 seq1 = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 3));
3593 if (!seq1)
3594 return NULL;
3595 seq2 = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 6));
3596 if (!seq2)
3597 return NULL;
3598
3599 return If(expression, seq1, seq2, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
3600 c->c_arena);
3601 }
3602 else if (s[2] == 'i') {
3603 int i, n_elif, has_else = 0;
3604 expr_ty expression;
3605 asdl_seq *suite_seq;
3606 asdl_seq *orelse = NULL;
3607 n_elif = NCH(n) - 4;
3608 /* must reference the child n_elif+1 since 'else' token is third,
3609 not fourth, child from the end. */
3610 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, (n_elif + 1))) == NAME
3611 && STR(CHILD(n, (n_elif + 1)))[2] == 's') {
3612 has_else = 1;
3613 n_elif -= 3;
3614 }
3615 n_elif /= 4;
3616
3617 if (has_else) {
3618 asdl_seq *suite_seq2;
3619
3620 orelse = _Py_asdl_seq_new(1, c->c_arena);
3621 if (!orelse)
3622 return NULL;
3623 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 6));
3624 if (!expression)
3625 return NULL;
3626 suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 4));
3627 if (!suite_seq)
3628 return NULL;
3629 suite_seq2 = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 1));
3630 if (!suite_seq2)
3631 return NULL;
3632
3633 asdl_seq_SET(orelse, 0,
3634 If(expression, suite_seq, suite_seq2,
3635 LINENO(CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 6)),
3636 CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 6)->n_col_offset,
3637 c->c_arena));
3638 /* the just-created orelse handled the last elif */
3639 n_elif--;
3640 }
3641
3642 for (i = 0; i < n_elif; i++) {
3643 int off = 5 + (n_elif - i - 1) * 4;
3644 asdl_seq *newobj = _Py_asdl_seq_new(1, c->c_arena);
3645 if (!newobj)
3646 return NULL;
3647 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, off));
3648 if (!expression)
3649 return NULL;
3650 suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, off + 2));
3651 if (!suite_seq)
3652 return NULL;
3653
3654 asdl_seq_SET(newobj, 0,
3655 If(expression, suite_seq, orelse,
3656 LINENO(CHILD(n, off)),
3657 CHILD(n, off)->n_col_offset, c->c_arena));
3658 orelse = newobj;
3659 }
3660 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
3661 if (!expression)
3662 return NULL;
3663 suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 3));
3664 if (!suite_seq)
3665 return NULL;
3666 return If(expression, suite_seq, orelse,
3667 LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3668 }
3669
3670 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
3671 "unexpected token in 'if' statement: %s", s);
3672 return NULL;
3673}
3674
3675static stmt_ty
3676ast_for_while_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3677{
3678 /* while_stmt: 'while' test ':' suite ['else' ':' suite] */
3679 REQ(n, while_stmt);
3680
3681 if (NCH(n) == 4) {
3682 expr_ty expression;
3683 asdl_seq *suite_seq;
3684
3685 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
3686 if (!expression)
3687 return NULL;
3688 suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 3));
3689 if (!suite_seq)
3690 return NULL;
3691 return While(expression, suite_seq, NULL, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3692 }
3693 else if (NCH(n) == 7) {
3694 expr_ty expression;
3695 asdl_seq *seq1, *seq2;
3696
3697 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 1));
3698 if (!expression)
3699 return NULL;
3700 seq1 = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 3));
3701 if (!seq1)
3702 return NULL;
3703 seq2 = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 6));
3704 if (!seq2)
3705 return NULL;
3706
3707 return While(expression, seq1, seq2, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3708 }
3709
3710 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
3711 "wrong number of tokens for 'while' statement: %d",
3712 NCH(n));
3713 return NULL;
3714}
3715
3716static stmt_ty
3717ast_for_for_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n, int is_async)
3718{
3719 asdl_seq *_target, *seq = NULL, *suite_seq;
3720 expr_ty expression;
3721 expr_ty target, first;
3722 const node *node_target;
3723 /* for_stmt: 'for' exprlist 'in' testlist ':' suite ['else' ':' suite] */
3724 REQ(n, for_stmt);
3725
3726 if (NCH(n) == 9) {
3727 seq = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 8));
3728 if (!seq)
3729 return NULL;
3730 }
3731
3732 node_target = CHILD(n, 1);
3733 _target = ast_for_exprlist(c, node_target, Store);
3734 if (!_target)
3735 return NULL;
3736 /* Check the # of children rather than the length of _target, since
3737 for x, in ... has 1 element in _target, but still requires a Tuple. */
3738 first = (expr_ty)asdl_seq_GET(_target, 0);
3739 if (NCH(node_target) == 1)
3740 target = first;
3741 else
3742 target = Tuple(_target, Store, first->lineno, first->col_offset, c->c_arena);
3743
3744 expression = ast_for_testlist(c, CHILD(n, 3));
3745 if (!expression)
3746 return NULL;
3747 suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 5));
3748 if (!suite_seq)
3749 return NULL;
3750
3751 if (is_async)
3752 return AsyncFor(target, expression, suite_seq, seq,
3753 LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
3754 c->c_arena);
3755 else
3756 return For(target, expression, suite_seq, seq,
3757 LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
3758 c->c_arena);
3759}
3760
3761static excepthandler_ty
3762ast_for_except_clause(struct compiling *c, const node *exc, node *body)
3763{
3764 /* except_clause: 'except' [test ['as' test]] */
3765 REQ(exc, except_clause);
3766 REQ(body, suite);
3767
3768 if (NCH(exc) == 1) {
3769 asdl_seq *suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, body);
3770 if (!suite_seq)
3771 return NULL;
3772
3773 return ExceptHandler(NULL, NULL, suite_seq, LINENO(exc),
3774 exc->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3775 }
3776 else if (NCH(exc) == 2) {
3777 expr_ty expression;
3778 asdl_seq *suite_seq;
3779
3780 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(exc, 1));
3781 if (!expression)
3782 return NULL;
3783 suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, body);
3784 if (!suite_seq)
3785 return NULL;
3786
3787 return ExceptHandler(expression, NULL, suite_seq, LINENO(exc),
3788 exc->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3789 }
3790 else if (NCH(exc) == 4) {
3791 asdl_seq *suite_seq;
3792 expr_ty expression;
3793 identifier e = NEW_IDENTIFIER(CHILD(exc, 3));
3794 if (!e)
3795 return NULL;
3796 if (forbidden_name(c, e, CHILD(exc, 3), 0))
3797 return NULL;
3798 expression = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(exc, 1));
3799 if (!expression)
3800 return NULL;
3801 suite_seq = ast_for_suite(c, body);
3802 if (!suite_seq)
3803 return NULL;
3804
3805 return ExceptHandler(expression, e, suite_seq, LINENO(exc),
3806 exc->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3807 }
3808
3809 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
3810 "wrong number of children for 'except' clause: %d",
3811 NCH(exc));
3812 return NULL;
3813}
3814
3815static stmt_ty
3816ast_for_try_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3817{
3818 const int nch = NCH(n);
3819 int n_except = (nch - 3)/3;
3820 asdl_seq *body, *handlers = NULL, *orelse = NULL, *finally = NULL;
3821
3822 REQ(n, try_stmt);
3823
3824 body = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, 2));
3825 if (body == NULL)
3826 return NULL;
3827
3828 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, nch - 3)) == NAME) {
3829 if (strcmp(STR(CHILD(n, nch - 3)), "finally") == 0) {
3830 if (nch >= 9 && TYPE(CHILD(n, nch - 6)) == NAME) {
3831 /* we can assume it's an "else",
3832 because nch >= 9 for try-else-finally and
3833 it would otherwise have a type of except_clause */
3834 orelse = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, nch - 4));
3835 if (orelse == NULL)
3836 return NULL;
3837 n_except--;
3838 }
3839
3840 finally = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, nch - 1));
3841 if (finally == NULL)
3842 return NULL;
3843 n_except--;
3844 }
3845 else {
3846 /* we can assume it's an "else",
3847 otherwise it would have a type of except_clause */
3848 orelse = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, nch - 1));
3849 if (orelse == NULL)
3850 return NULL;
3851 n_except--;
3852 }
3853 }
3854 else if (TYPE(CHILD(n, nch - 3)) != except_clause) {
3855 ast_error(c, n, "malformed 'try' statement");
3856 return NULL;
3857 }
3858
3859 if (n_except > 0) {
3860 int i;
3861 /* process except statements to create a try ... except */
3862 handlers = _Py_asdl_seq_new(n_except, c->c_arena);
3863 if (handlers == NULL)
3864 return NULL;
3865
3866 for (i = 0; i < n_except; i++) {
3867 excepthandler_ty e = ast_for_except_clause(c, CHILD(n, 3 + i * 3),
3868 CHILD(n, 5 + i * 3));
3869 if (!e)
3870 return NULL;
3871 asdl_seq_SET(handlers, i, e);
3872 }
3873 }
3874
3875 assert(finally != NULL || asdl_seq_LEN(handlers));
3876 return Try(body, handlers, orelse, finally, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3877}
3878
3879/* with_item: test ['as' expr] */
3880static withitem_ty
3881ast_for_with_item(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3882{
3883 expr_ty context_expr, optional_vars = NULL;
3884
3885 REQ(n, with_item);
3886 context_expr = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 0));
3887 if (!context_expr)
3888 return NULL;
3889 if (NCH(n) == 3) {
3890 optional_vars = ast_for_expr(c, CHILD(n, 2));
3891
3892 if (!optional_vars) {
3893 return NULL;
3894 }
3895 if (!set_context(c, optional_vars, Store, n)) {
3896 return NULL;
3897 }
3898 }
3899
3900 return withitem(context_expr, optional_vars, c->c_arena);
3901}
3902
3903/* with_stmt: 'with' with_item (',' with_item)* ':' suite */
3904static stmt_ty
3905ast_for_with_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n, int is_async)
3906{
3907 int i, n_items;
3908 asdl_seq *items, *body;
3909
3910 REQ(n, with_stmt);
3911
3912 n_items = (NCH(n) - 2) / 2;
3913 items = _Py_asdl_seq_new(n_items, c->c_arena);
3914 if (!items)
3915 return NULL;
3916 for (i = 1; i < NCH(n) - 2; i += 2) {
3917 withitem_ty item = ast_for_with_item(c, CHILD(n, i));
3918 if (!item)
3919 return NULL;
3920 asdl_seq_SET(items, (i - 1) / 2, item);
3921 }
3922
3923 body = ast_for_suite(c, CHILD(n, NCH(n) - 1));
3924 if (!body)
3925 return NULL;
3926
3927 if (is_async)
3928 return AsyncWith(items, body, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3929 else
3930 return With(items, body, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3931}

3933static stmt_ty
3934ast_for_classdef(struct compiling *c, const node *n, asdl_seq *decorator_seq)
3935{
3936 /* classdef: 'class' NAME ['(' arglist ')'] ':' suite */
3937 PyObject *classname;
3938 asdl_seq *s;
3939 string docstring;
3940 expr_ty call;
3941
3942 REQ(n, classdef);
3943
3944 if (NCH(n) == 4) { /* class NAME ':' suite */
3945 s = ast_for_body(c, CHILD(n, 3), &docstring);
3946 if (!s)
3947 return NULL;
3948 classname = NEW_IDENTIFIER(CHILD(n, 1));
3949 if (!classname)
3950 return NULL;
3951 if (forbidden_name(c, classname, CHILD(n, 3), 0))
3952 return NULL;
3953 return ClassDef(classname, NULL, NULL, s, decorator_seq, docstring,
3954 LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3955 }
3956
3957 if (TYPE(CHILD(n, 3)) == RPAR) { /* class NAME '(' ')' ':' suite */
3958 s = ast_for_body(c, CHILD(n, 5), &docstring);
3959 if (!s)
3960 return NULL;
3961 classname = NEW_IDENTIFIER(CHILD(n, 1));
3962 if (!classname)
3963 return NULL;
3964 if (forbidden_name(c, classname, CHILD(n, 3), 0))
3965 return NULL;
3966 return ClassDef(classname, NULL, NULL, s, decorator_seq, docstring,
3967 LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3968 }
3969
3970 /* class NAME '(' arglist ')' ':' suite */
3971 /* build up a fake Call node so we can extract its pieces */
3972 {
3973 PyObject *dummy_name;
3974 expr_ty dummy;
3975 dummy_name = NEW_IDENTIFIER(CHILD(n, 1));
3976 if (!dummy_name)
3977 return NULL;
3978 dummy = Name(dummy_name, Load, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
3979 call = ast_for_call(c, CHILD(n, 3), dummy);
3980 if (!call)
3981 return NULL;
3982 }
3983 s = ast_for_body(c, CHILD(n, 6), &docstring);
3984 if (!s)
3985 return NULL;
3986 classname = NEW_IDENTIFIER(CHILD(n, 1));
3987 if (!classname)
3988 return NULL;
3989 if (forbidden_name(c, classname, CHILD(n, 1), 0))
3990 return NULL;
3991
3992 return ClassDef(classname, call->v.Call.args, call->v.Call.keywords, s,
3993 decorator_seq, docstring, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
3994 c->c_arena);
3995}
3996
3997static stmt_ty
3998ast_for_stmt(struct compiling *c, const node *n)
3999{
4000 if (TYPE(n) == stmt) {
4001 assert(NCH(n) == 1);
4002 n = CHILD(n, 0);
4003 }
4004 if (TYPE(n) == simple_stmt) {
4005 assert(num_stmts(n) == 1);
4006 n = CHILD(n, 0);
4007 }
4008 if (TYPE(n) == small_stmt) {
4009 n = CHILD(n, 0);
4010 /* small_stmt: expr_stmt | del_stmt | pass_stmt | flow_stmt
4011 | import_stmt | global_stmt | nonlocal_stmt | assert_stmt
4012 */
4013 switch (TYPE(n)) {
4014 case expr_stmt:
4015 return ast_for_expr_stmt(c, n);
4016 case del_stmt:
4017 return ast_for_del_stmt(c, n);
4018 case pass_stmt:
4019 return Pass(LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset, c->c_arena);
4020 case flow_stmt:
4021 return ast_for_flow_stmt(c, n);
4022 case import_stmt:
4023 return ast_for_import_stmt(c, n);
4024 case global_stmt:
4025 return ast_for_global_stmt(c, n);
4026 case nonlocal_stmt:
4027 return ast_for_nonlocal_stmt(c, n);
4028 case assert_stmt:
4029 return ast_for_assert_stmt(c, n);
4030 default:
4031 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
4032 "unhandled small_stmt: TYPE=%d NCH=%d\n",
4033 TYPE(n), NCH(n));
4034 return NULL;
4035 }
4036 }
4037 else {
4038 /* compound_stmt: if_stmt | while_stmt | for_stmt | try_stmt
4039 | funcdef | classdef | decorated | async_stmt
4040 */
4041 node *ch = CHILD(n, 0);
4042 REQ(n, compound_stmt);
4043 switch (TYPE(ch)) {
4044 case if_stmt:
4045 return ast_for_if_stmt(c, ch);
4046 case while_stmt:
4047 return ast_for_while_stmt(c, ch);
4048 case for_stmt:
4049 return ast_for_for_stmt(c, ch, 0);
4050 case try_stmt:
4051 return ast_for_try_stmt(c, ch);
4052 case with_stmt:
4053 return ast_for_with_stmt(c, ch, 0);
4054 case funcdef:
4055 return ast_for_funcdef(c, ch, NULL);
4056 case classdef:
4057 return ast_for_classdef(c, ch, NULL);
4058 case decorated:
4059 return ast_for_decorated(c, ch);
4060 case async_stmt:
4061 return ast_for_async_stmt(c, ch);
4062 default:
4063 PyErr_Format(PyExc_SystemError,
4064 "unhandled small_stmt: TYPE=%d NCH=%d\n",
4065 TYPE(n), NCH(n));
4066 return NULL;
4067 }
4068 }
4069}
4070
4071static PyObject *
4072parsenumber_raw(struct compiling *c, const char *s)
4073{
4074 const char *end;
4075 long x;
4076 double dx;
4077 Py_complex compl;
4078 int imflag;
4079
4080 assert(s != NULL);
4081 errno = 0;
4082 end = s + strlen(s) - 1;
4083 imflag = *end == 'j' || *end == 'J';
4084 if (s[0] == '0') {
4085 x = (long) PyOS_strtoul(s, (char **)&end, 0);
4086 if (x < 0 && errno == 0) {
4087 return PyLong_FromString(s, (char **)0, 0);
4088 }
4089 }
4090 else
4091 x = PyOS_strtol(s, (char **)&end, 0);
4092 if (*end == '\0') {
4093 if (errno != 0)
4094 return PyLong_FromString(s, (char **)0, 0);
4095 return PyLong_FromLong(x);
4096 }
4097 /* XXX Huge floats may silently fail */
4098 if (imflag) {
4099 compl.real = 0.;
4100 compl.imag = PyOS_string_to_double(s, (char **)&end, NULL);
4101 if (compl.imag == -1.0 && PyErr_Occurred())
4102 return NULL;
4103 return PyComplex_FromCComplex(compl);
4104 }
4105 else
4106 {
4107 dx = PyOS_string_to_double(s, NULL, NULL);
4108 if (dx == -1.0 && PyErr_Occurred())
4109 return NULL;
4110 return PyFloat_FromDouble(dx);
4111 }
4112}
4113
4114static PyObject *
4115parsenumber(struct compiling *c, const char *s)
4116{
4117 char *dup, *end;
4118 PyObject *res = NULL;
4119
4120 assert(s != NULL);
4121
4122 if (strchr(s, '_') == NULL) {
4123 return parsenumber_raw(c, s);
4124 }
4125 /* Create a duplicate without underscores. */
4126 dup = PyMem_Malloc(strlen(s) + 1);
4127 end = dup;
4128 for (; *s; s++) {
4129 if (*s != '_') {
4130 *end++ = *s;
4131 }
4132 }
4133 *end = '\0';
4134 res = parsenumber_raw(c, dup);
4135 PyMem_Free(dup);
4136 return res;
4137}
4138
4139static PyObject *
4140decode_utf8(struct compiling *c, const char **sPtr, const char *end)
4141{
4142 const char *s, *t;
4143 t = s = *sPtr;
4144 /* while (s < end && *s != '\\') s++; */ /* inefficient for u".." */
4145 while (s < end && (*s & 0x80)) s++;
4146 *sPtr = s;
4147 return PyUnicode_DecodeUTF8(t, s - t, NULL);
4148}
4149
4150static int
4151warn_invalid_escape_sequence(struct compiling *c, const node *n,
4152 char first_invalid_escape_char)
4153{
4154 PyObject *msg = PyUnicode_FromFormat("invalid escape sequence \\%c",
4155 first_invalid_escape_char);
4156 if (msg == NULL) {
4157 return -1;
4158 }
4159 if (PyErr_WarnExplicitObject(PyExc_DeprecationWarning, msg,
4160 c->c_filename, LINENO(n),
4161 NULL, NULL) < 0 &&
4162 PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_DeprecationWarning))
4163 {
4164 const char *s;
4165
4166 /* Replace the DeprecationWarning exception with a SyntaxError
4167 to get a more accurate error report */
4168 PyErr_Clear();
4169
4170 s = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(msg);
4171 if (s != NULL) {
4172 ast_error(c, n, s);
4173 }
4174 Py_DECREF(msg);
4175 return -1;
4176 }
4177 Py_DECREF(msg);
4178 return 0;
4179}
4180
4181static PyObject *
4182decode_unicode_with_escapes(struct compiling *c, const node *n, const char *s,
4183 size_t len)
4184{
4185 PyObject *v, *u;
4186 char *buf;
4187 char *p;
4188 const char *end;
4189
4190 /* check for integer overflow */
4191 if (len > SIZE_MAX / 6)
4192 return NULL;
4193 /* "" (2 bytes) may become "\U000000E4" (10 bytes), or 1:5
4194 "\" (3 bytes) may become "\u005c\U000000E4" (16 bytes), or ~1:6 */
4195 u = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize((char *)NULL, len * 6);
4196 if (u == NULL)
4197 return NULL;
4198 p = buf = PyBytes_AsString(u);
4199 end = s + len;
4200 while (s < end) {
4201 if (*s == '\\') {
4202 *p++ = *s++;
4203 if (s >= end || *s & 0x80) {
4204 strcpy(p, "u005c");
4205 p += 5;
4206 if (s >= end)
4207 break;
4208 }
4209 }
4210 if (*s & 0x80) { /* XXX inefficient */
4211 PyObject *w;
4212 int kind;
4213 void *data;
4214 Py_ssize_t len, i;
4215 w = decode_utf8(c, &s, end);
4216 if (w == NULL) {
4217 Py_DECREF(u);
4218 return NULL;
4219 }
4220 kind = PyUnicode_KIND(w);
4221 data = PyUnicode_DATA(w);
4222 len = PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(w);
4223 for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
4224 Py_UCS4 chr = PyUnicode_READ(kind, data, i);
4225 sprintf(p, "\\U%08x", chr);
4226 p += 10;
4227 }
4228 /* Should be impossible to overflow */
4229 assert(p - buf <= PyBytes_GET_SIZE(u));
4230 Py_DECREF(w);
4231 } else {
4232 *p++ = *s++;
4233 }
4234 }
4235 len = p - buf;
4236 s = buf;
4237
4238 const char *first_invalid_escape;
4239 v = _PyUnicode_DecodeUnicodeEscape(s, len, NULL, &first_invalid_escape);
4240
4241 if (v != NULL && first_invalid_escape != NULL) {
4242 if (warn_invalid_escape_sequence(c, n, *first_invalid_escape) < 0) {
4243 /* We have not decref u before because first_invalid_escape points
4244 inside u. */
4245 Py_XDECREF(u);
4246 Py_DECREF(v);
4247 return NULL;
4248 }
4249 }
4250 Py_XDECREF(u);
4251 return v;
4252}
4253
4254static PyObject *
4255decode_bytes_with_escapes(struct compiling *c, const node *n, const char *s,
4256 size_t len)
4257{
4258 const char *first_invalid_escape;
4259 PyObject *result = _PyBytes_DecodeEscape(s, len, NULL, 0, NULL,
4260 &first_invalid_escape);
4261 if (result == NULL)
4262 return NULL;
4263
4264 if (first_invalid_escape != NULL) {
4265 if (warn_invalid_escape_sequence(c, n, *first_invalid_escape) < 0) {
4266 Py_DECREF(result);
4267 return NULL;
4268 }
4269 }
4270 return result;
4271}
4272
4273/* Compile this expression in to an expr_ty. Add parens around the
4274 expression, in order to allow leading spaces in the expression. */
4275static expr_ty
4276fstring_compile_expr(const char *expr_start, const char *expr_end,
4277 struct compiling *c, const node *n)
4278
4279{
4280 PyCompilerFlags cf;
4281 mod_ty mod;
4282 char *str;
4283 Py_ssize_t len;
4284 const char *s;
4285
4286 assert(expr_end >= expr_start);
4287 assert(*(expr_start-1) == '{');
4288 assert(*expr_end == '}' || *expr_end == '!' || *expr_end == ':');
4289
4290 /* If the substring is all whitespace, it's an error. We need to catch
4291 this here, and not when we call PyParser_ASTFromString, because turning
4292 the expression '' in to '()' would go from being invalid to valid. */
4293 for (s = expr_start; s != expr_end; s++) {
4294 char c = *s;
4295 /* The Python parser ignores only the following whitespace
4296 characters (\r already is converted to \n). */
4297 if (!(c == ' ' || c == '\t' || c == '\n' || c == '\f')) {
4298 break;
4299 }
4300 }
4301 if (s == expr_end) {
4302 ast_error(c, n, "f-string: empty expression not allowed");
4303 return NULL;
4304 }
4305
4306 len = expr_end - expr_start;
4307 /* Allocate 3 extra bytes: open paren, close paren, null byte. */
4308 str = PyMem_RawMalloc(len + 3);
4309 if (str == NULL)
4310 return NULL;
4311
4312 str[0] = '(';
4313 memcpy(str+1, expr_start, len);
4314 str[len+1] = ')';
4315 str[len+2] = 0;
4316
4317 cf.cf_flags = PyCF_ONLY_AST;
4318 mod = PyParser_ASTFromString(str, "<fstring>",
4319 Py_eval_input, &cf, c->c_arena);
4320 PyMem_RawFree(str);
4321 if (!mod)
4322 return NULL;
4323 return mod->v.Expression.body;
4324}
4325
4326/* Return -1 on error.
4327
4328 Return 0 if we reached the end of the literal.
4329
4330 Return 1 if we haven't reached the end of the literal, but we want
4331 the caller to process the literal up to this point. Used for
4332 doubled braces.
4333*/
4334static int
4335fstring_find_literal(const char **str, const char *end, int raw,
4336 PyObject **literal, int recurse_lvl,
4337 struct compiling *c, const node *n)
4338{
4339 /* Get any literal string. It ends when we hit an un-doubled left
4340 brace (which isn't part of a unicode name escape such as
4341 "\N{EULER CONSTANT}"), or the end of the string. */
4342
4343 const char *s = *str;
4344 const char *literal_start = s;
4345 int result = 0;
4346
4347 assert(*literal == NULL);
4348 while (s < end) {
4349 char ch = *s++;
4350 if (!raw && ch == '\\' && s < end) {
4351 ch = *s++;
4352 if (ch == 'N') {
4353 if (s < end && *s++ == '{') {
4354 while (s < end && *s++ != '}') {
4355 }
4356 continue;
4357 }
4358 break;
4359 }
4360 if (ch == '{' && warn_invalid_escape_sequence(c, n, ch) < 0) {
4361 return -1;
4362 }
4363 }
4364 if (ch == '{' || ch == '}') {
4365 /* Check for doubled braces, but only at the top level. If
4366 we checked at every level, then f'{0:{3}}' would fail
4367 with the two closing braces. */
4368 if (recurse_lvl == 0) {
4369 if (s < end && *s == ch) {
4370 /* We're going to tell the caller that the literal ends
4371 here, but that they should continue scanning. But also
4372 skip over the second brace when we resume scanning. */
4373 *str = s + 1;
4374 result = 1;
4375 goto done;
4376 }
4377
4378 /* Where a single '{' is the start of a new expression, a
4379 single '}' is not allowed. */
4380 if (ch == '}') {
4381 *str = s - 1;
4382 ast_error(c, n, "f-string: single '}' is not allowed");
4383 return -1;
4384 }
4385 }
4386 /* We're either at a '{', which means we're starting another
4387 expression; or a '}', which means we're at the end of this
4388 f-string (for a nested format_spec). */
4389 s--;
4390 break;
4391 }
4392 }
4393 *str = s;
4394 assert(s <= end);
4395 assert(s == end || *s == '{' || *s == '}');
4396done:
4397 if (literal_start != s) {
4398 if (raw)
4399 *literal = PyUnicode_DecodeUTF8Stateful(literal_start,
4400 s - literal_start,
4401 NULL, NULL);
4402 else
4403 *literal = decode_unicode_with_escapes(c, n, literal_start,
4404 s - literal_start);
4405 if (!*literal)
4406 return -1;
4407 }
4408 return result;
4409}
4410
4411/* Forward declaration because parsing is recursive. */
4412static expr_ty
4413fstring_parse(const char **str, const char *end, int raw, int recurse_lvl,
4414 struct compiling *c, const node *n);
4415
4416/* Parse the f-string at *str, ending at end. We know *str starts an
4417 expression (so it must be a '{'). Returns the FormattedValue node,
4418 which includes the expression, conversion character, and
4419 format_spec expression.
4420
4421 Note that I don't do a perfect job here: I don't make sure that a
4422 closing brace doesn't match an opening paren, for example. It
4423 doesn't need to error on all invalid expressions, just correctly
4424 find the end of all valid ones. Any errors inside the expression
4425 will be caught when we parse it later. */
4426static int
4427fstring_find_expr(const char **str, const char *end, int raw, int recurse_lvl,
4428 expr_ty *expression, struct compiling *c, const node *n)
4429{
4430 /* Return -1 on error, else 0. */
4431
4432 const char *expr_start;
4433 const char *expr_end;
4434 expr_ty simple_expression;
4435 expr_ty format_spec = NULL; /* Optional format specifier. */
4436 int conversion = -1; /* The conversion char. -1 if not specified. */
4437
4438 /* 0 if we're not in a string, else the quote char we're trying to
4439 match (single or double quote). */
4440 char quote_char = 0;
4441
4442 /* If we're inside a string, 1=normal, 3=triple-quoted. */
4443 int string_type = 0;
4444
4445 /* Keep track of nesting level for braces/parens/brackets in
4446 expressions. */
4447 Py_ssize_t nested_depth = 0;
4448
4449 /* Can only nest one level deep. */
4450 if (recurse_lvl >= 2) {
4451 ast_error(c, n, "f-string: expressions nested too deeply");
4452 return -1;
4453 }
4454
4455 /* The first char must be a left brace, or we wouldn't have gotten
4456 here. Skip over it. */
4457 assert(**str == '{');
4458 *str += 1;
4459
4460 expr_start = *str;
4461 for (; *str < end; (*str)++) {
4462 char ch;
4463
4464 /* Loop invariants. */
4465 assert(nested_depth >= 0);
4466 assert(*str >= expr_start && *str < end);
4467 if (quote_char)
4468 assert(string_type == 1 || string_type == 3);
4469 else
4470 assert(string_type == 0);
4471
4472 ch = **str;
4473 /* Nowhere inside an expression is a backslash allowed. */
4474 if (ch == '\\') {
4475 /* Error: can't include a backslash character, inside
4476 parens or strings or not. */
4477 ast_error(c, n, "f-string expression part "
4478 "cannot include a backslash");
4479 return -1;
4480 }
4481 if (quote_char) {
4482 /* We're inside a string. See if we're at the end. */
4483 /* This code needs to implement the same non-error logic
4484 as tok_get from tokenizer.c, at the letter_quote
4485 label. To actually share that code would be a
4486 nightmare. But, it's unlikely to change and is small,
4487 so duplicate it here. Note we don't need to catch all
4488 of the errors, since they'll be caught when parsing the
4489 expression. We just need to match the non-error
4490 cases. Thus we can ignore \n in single-quoted strings,
4491 for example. Or non-terminated strings. */
4492 if (ch == quote_char) {
4493 /* Does this match the string_type (single or triple
4494 quoted)? */
4495 if (string_type == 3) {
4496 if (*str+2 < end && *(*str+1) == ch && *(*str+2) == ch) {
4497 /* We're at the end of a triple quoted string. */
4498 *str += 2;
4499 string_type = 0;
4500 quote_char = 0;
4501 continue;
4502 }
4503 } else {
4504 /* We're at the end of a normal string. */
4505 quote_char = 0;
4506 string_type = 0;
4507 continue;
4508 }
4509 }
4510 } else if (ch == '\'' || ch == '"') {
4511 /* Is this a triple quoted string? */
4512 if (*str+2 < end && *(*str+1) == ch && *(*str+2) == ch) {
4513 string_type = 3;
4514 *str += 2;
4515 } else {
4516 /* Start of a normal string. */
4517 string_type = 1;
4518 }
4519 /* Start looking for the end of the string. */
4520 quote_char = ch;
4521 } else if (ch == '[' || ch == '{' || ch == '(') {
4522 nested_depth++;
4523 } else if (nested_depth != 0 &&
4524 (ch == ']' || ch == '}' || ch == ')')) {
4525 nested_depth--;
4526 } else if (ch == '#') {
4527 /* Error: can't include a comment character, inside parens
4528 or not. */
4529 ast_error(c, n, "f-string expression part cannot include '#'");
4530 return -1;
4531 } else if (nested_depth == 0 &&
4532 (ch == '!' || ch == ':' || ch == '}')) {
4533 /* First, test for the special case of "!=". Since '=' is
4534 not an allowed conversion character, nothing is lost in
4535 this test. */
4536 if (ch == '!' && *str+1 < end && *(*str+1) == '=') {
4537 /* This isn't a conversion character, just continue. */
4538 continue;
4539 }
4540 /* Normal way out of this loop. */
4541 break;
4542 } else {
4543 /* Just consume this char and loop around. */
4544 }
4545 }
4546 expr_end = *str;
4547 /* If we leave this loop in a string or with mismatched parens, we
4548 don't care. We'll get a syntax error when compiling the
4549 expression. But, we can produce a better error message, so
4550 let's just do that.*/
4551 if (quote_char) {
4552 ast_error(c, n, "f-string: unterminated string");
4553 return -1;
4554 }
4555 if (nested_depth) {
4556 ast_error(c, n, "f-string: mismatched '(', '{', or '['");
4557 return -1;
4558 }
4559
4560 if (*str >= end)
4561 goto unexpected_end_of_string;
4562
4563 /* Compile the expression as soon as possible, so we show errors
4564 related to the expression before errors related to the
4565 conversion or format_spec. */
4566 simple_expression = fstring_compile_expr(expr_start, expr_end, c, n);
4567 if (!simple_expression)
4568 return -1;
4569
4570 /* Check for a conversion char, if present. */
4571 if (**str == '!') {
4572 *str += 1;
4573 if (*str >= end)
4574 goto unexpected_end_of_string;
4575
4576 conversion = **str;
4577 *str += 1;
4578
4579 /* Validate the conversion. */
4580 if (!(conversion == 's' || conversion == 'r'
4581 || conversion == 'a')) {
4582 ast_error(c, n, "f-string: invalid conversion character: "
4583 "expected 's', 'r', or 'a'");
4584 return -1;
4585 }
4586 }
4587
4588 /* Check for the format spec, if present. */
4589 if (*str >= end)
4590 goto unexpected_end_of_string;
4591 if (**str == ':') {
4592 *str += 1;
4593 if (*str >= end)
4594 goto unexpected_end_of_string;
4595
4596 /* Parse the format spec. */
4597 format_spec = fstring_parse(str, end, raw, recurse_lvl+1, c, n);
4598 if (!format_spec)
4599 return -1;
4600 }
4601
4602 if (*str >= end || **str != '}')
4603 goto unexpected_end_of_string;
4604
4605 /* We're at a right brace. Consume it. */
4606 assert(*str < end);
4607 assert(**str == '}');
4608 *str += 1;
4609
4610 /* And now create the FormattedValue node that represents this
4611 entire expression with the conversion and format spec. */
4612 *expression = FormattedValue(simple_expression, conversion,
4613 format_spec, LINENO(n), n->n_col_offset,
4614 c->c_arena);
4615 if (!*expression)
4616 return -1;
4617
4618 return 0;
4619
4620unexpected_end_of_string:
4621 ast_error(c, n, "f-string: expecting '}'");
4622 return -1;
4623}
4624
4625/* Return -1 on error.
4626
4627 Return 0 if we have a literal (possible zero length) and an
4628 expression (zero length if at the end of the string.
4629
4630 Return 1 if we have a literal, but no expression, and we want the
4631 caller to call us again. This is used to deal with doubled
4632 braces.
4633
4634 When called multiple times on the string 'a{{b{0}c', this function
4635 will return:
4636
4637 1. the literal 'a{' with no expression, and a return value
4638 of 1. Despite the fact that there's no expression, the return
4639 value of 1 means we're not finished yet.
4640
4641 2. the literal 'b' and the expression '0', with a return value of
4642 0. The fact that there's an expression means we're not finished.
4643
4644 3. literal 'c' with no expression and a return value of 0. The
4645 combination of the return value of 0 with no expression means
4646 we're finished.
4647*/
4648static int
4649fstring_find_literal_and_expr(const char **str, const char *end, int raw,
4650 int recurse_lvl, PyObject **literal,
4651 expr_ty *expression,
4652 struct compiling *c, const node *n)
4653{
4654 int result;
4655
4656 assert(*literal == NULL && *expression == NULL);
4657
4658 /* Get any literal string. */
4659 result = fstring_find_literal(str, end, raw, literal, recurse_lvl, c, n);
4660 if (result < 0)
4661 goto error;
4662
4663 assert(result == 0 || result == 1);
4664
4665 if (result == 1)
4666 /* We have a literal, but don't look at the expression. */
4667 return 1;
4668
4669 if (*str >= end || **str == '}')
4670 /* We're at the end of the string or the end of a nested
4671 f-string: no expression. The top-level error case where we
4672 expect to be at the end of the string but we're at a '}' is
4673 handled later. */
4674 return 0;
4675
4676 /* We must now be the start of an expression, on a '{'. */
4677 assert(**str == '{');
4678
4679 if (fstring_find_expr(str, end, raw, recurse_lvl, expression, c, n) < 0)
4680 goto error;
4681
4682 return 0;
4683
4684error:
4685 Py_CLEAR(*literal);
4686 return -1;
4687}
4688
4689#define EXPRLIST_N_CACHED 64
4690
4691typedef struct {
4692 /* Incrementally build an array of expr_ty, so be used in an
4693 asdl_seq. Cache some small but reasonably sized number of
4694 expr_ty's, and then after that start dynamically allocating,
4695 doubling the number allocated each time. Note that the f-string
4696 f'{0}a{1}' contains 3 expr_ty's: 2 FormattedValue's, and one
4697 Str for the literal 'a'. So you add expr_ty's about twice as
4698 fast as you add exressions in an f-string. */
4699
4700 Py_ssize_t allocated; /* Number we've allocated. */
4701 Py_ssize_t size; /* Number we've used. */
4702 expr_ty *p; /* Pointer to the memory we're actually
4703 using. Will point to 'data' until we
4704 start dynamically allocating. */
4705 expr_ty data[EXPRLIST_N_CACHED];
4706} ExprList;
4707
4708#ifdef NDEBUG
4709#define ExprList_check_invariants(l)
4710#else
4711static void
4712ExprList_check_invariants(ExprList *l)
4713{
4714 /* Check our invariants. Make sure this object is "live", and
4715 hasn't been deallocated. */
4716 assert(l->size >= 0);
4717 assert(l->p != NULL);
4718 if (l->size <= EXPRLIST_N_CACHED)
4719 assert(l->data == l->p);
4720}
4721#endif
4722
4723static void
4724ExprList_Init(ExprList *l)
4725{
4726 l->allocated = EXPRLIST_N_CACHED;
4727 l->size = 0;
4728
4729 /* Until we start allocating dynamically, p points to data. */
4730 l->p = l->data;
4731
4732 ExprList_check_invariants(l);
4733}
4734
4735static int
4736ExprList_Append(ExprList *l, expr_ty exp)
4737{
4738 ExprList_check_invariants(l);
4739 if (l->size >= l->allocated) {
4740 /* We need to alloc (or realloc) the memory. */
4741 Py_ssize_t new_size = l->allocated * 2;
4742
4743 /* See if we've ever allocated anything dynamically. */
4744 if (l->p == l->data) {
4745 Py_ssize_t i;
4746 /* We're still using the cached data. Switch to
4747 alloc-ing. */
4748 l->p = PyMem_RawMalloc(sizeof(expr_ty) * new_size);
4749 if (!l->p)
4750 return -1;
4751 /* Copy the cached data into the new buffer. */
4752 for (i = 0; i < l->size; i++)
4753 l->p[i] = l->data[i];
4754 } else {
4755 /* Just realloc. */
4756 expr_ty *tmp = PyMem_RawRealloc(l->p, sizeof(expr_ty) * new_size);
4757 if (!tmp) {
4758 PyMem_RawFree(l->p);
4759 l->p = NULL;
4760 return -1;
4761 }
4762 l->p = tmp;
4763 }
4764
4765 l->allocated = new_size;
4766 assert(l->allocated == 2 * l->size);
4767 }
4768
4769 l->p[l->size++] = exp;
4770
4771 ExprList_check_invariants(l);
4772 return 0;
4773}
4774
4775static void
4776ExprList_Dealloc(ExprList *l)
4777{
4778 ExprList_check_invariants(l);
4779
4780 /* If there's been an error, or we've never dynamically allocated,
4781 do nothing. */
4782 if (!l->p || l->p == l->data) {
4783 /* Do nothing. */
4784 } else {
4785 /* We have dynamically allocated. Free the memory. */
4786 PyMem_RawFree(l->p);
4787 }
4788 l->p = NULL;
4789 l->size = -1;
4790}
4791
4792static asdl_seq *
4793ExprList_Finish(ExprList *l, PyArena *arena)
4794{
4795 asdl_seq *seq;
4796
4797 ExprList_check_invariants(l);
4798
4799 /* Allocate the asdl_seq and copy the expressions in to it. */
4800 seq = _Py_asdl_seq_new(l->size, arena);
4801 if (seq) {
4802 Py_ssize_t i;
4803 for (i = 0; i < l->size; i++)
4804 asdl_seq_SET(seq, i, l->p[i]);
4805 }
4806 ExprList_Dealloc(l);
4807 return seq;
4808}

4810/* The FstringParser is designed to add a mix of strings and
4811 f-strings, and concat them together as needed. Ultimately, it
4812 generates an expr_ty. */
4813typedef struct {
4814 PyObject *last_str;
4815 ExprList expr_list;
4816 int fmode;
4817} FstringParser;
4818
4819#ifdef NDEBUG
4820#define FstringParser_check_invariants(state)
4821#else
4822static void
4823FstringParser_check_invariants(FstringParser *state)
4824{
4825 if (state->last_str)
4826 assert(PyUnicode_CheckExact(state->last_str));
4827 ExprList_check_invariants(&state->expr_list);
4828}
4829#endif
4830
4831static void
4832FstringParser_Init(FstringParser *state)
4833{
4834 state->last_str = NULL;
4835 state->fmode = 0;
4836 ExprList_Init(&state->expr_list);
4837 FstringParser_check_invariants(state);
4838}
4839
4840static void
4841FstringParser_Dealloc(FstringParser *state)
4842{
4843 FstringParser_check_invariants(state);
4844
4845 Py_XDECREF(state->last_str);
4846 ExprList_Dealloc(&state->expr_list);
4847}
